ranked choice voting is democratic and representative. instead of just voting for one candidates, you vote for 5 in order of your preference

what is ranked choice voting? instead of picking just one candidate, rank 5 candidates in order of preference. rank all 5! do not leave any blank. 1st choice is your favorite, second is your backup, third is your next favorite and so on up to five.

fill in your whole ballot with 5 candidates. only list the candidates you would be happy with for mayor, public advocate, city council, and borough president. do not leave spaces on your ballot blank. do not vote for candidates you don't like

how it works: count 1st choices: all the first choice votes are counted. if someone gets more than 50% they win. no one gets 50%: the candidate with the fewest first choice votes is eliminated. anyone who picked that person as number 1 has their vote go to their second choice. repeat until one candidate has over 50% of the vote

why people like it: you can vote honestly without worrying about spoilers. encourages candidates to appeal to more voters, not just their base. promotes more civil campaigns. allows voters to choose the best candidates, not the lesser of two evils. empowers third parties to participate on equal footing. votes are counted representatively. allows candidates with similar values to tea up and encourage voters to rank them first. like the hunger games, candidates can create alliances against common enemies.

how to fill out your ballot: pick your first choice and completely fill out the oval next to their name under the first choice column. rank your top five candidates, do not leave any space blank. do not rank anyone you don't want to represent you

remember ranking multiple candidates doesn't hurt your favorite candidate. it only stretches your vote further. if you rank one candidate multiple times, only your first choice will count. this will make way for a candidate you can't stand to win. if you give multiple candidates the same ranking, your ballot will be invalidated. if you make a mistake on your ballot, just ask a poll worker for a new one
